\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}=100\times(ln(P_{t})-ln(P_{t-1}))$
\end_inset

.
 Let's assume a 
\begin_inset Formula $K\times1$
\end_inset

 vector 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

 of predictors.
 Our objective is to predict inflation 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 periods forwards 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t+h}$
\end_inset

,
 which can we viewed as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi_{t+h}=F_{h}(X_{t},\gamma)+\epsilon_{t+h}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $h=1,...,H$
\end_inset

 is the forecast horizon.
 
\begin_inset Formula $F(.)$
\end_inset

 is the relationship between inflation and its predictors,
 which could either linear or non-linear,
 depending on the model being used,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 represents both parameters and hyperpameters of the ML models and 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{t+h}$
\end_inset

 is the forecast error.
 
\end_layout

