 the Diebold-Mariano statistic is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
DM=H^{1/2}\frac{\sum_{j=1}^{H}d_{j}/H}{\sigma_{d}}=H^{1/2}\frac{\bar{d}}{\sigma_{d}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{d}$
\end_inset

 is the variance of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{d}$
\end_inset

